      Accessibility and inclusive design
      Everyone, no matter their profession, has specific roles and responsibilites to make sure DfE services are accessible.






    Understanding Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)





              Implementing WCAG

            Information about each WCAG guideline, what it means, how to implement and test.





              Draft 2.2 WCAG changes

            Summary of the new success criteria in WCAG 2.2 describing them in simple terms and how to meet them.





    Guidance





              Laws and regulations

            Accessibility requirements are enforced through different legislation and standards, find out what they are and how they apply.





              Inclusive design

            Consider who you are designing for and reduce unconscious biases.





              Roles and responsibilites

            Accessibility requirements are enforced through different legislation and standards, find out what they are and how they apply.




              Training

            Training resources for learning about accessibility across professions.





              Tools

            How to assure your service is compliant with accessibility regulations through testing and independent audits.

